instance

public static Holdbacks instance()

Parameters:

emptyInstance

public static void emptyInstance()
Empty whole the Holdbacks before the XML load. We just drop the singleton and create a new one.

createHoldback

public boolean createHoldback(java.lang.String position,
                              int lod)
Creates Holdback at the location specified by its id. This method can be called from the gui thread. Since the code is executed asynchronously, there is no way how to return the possible error, so call the method prevalidteHoldback fisrt to do at least the basic checks, before calling this one.

Parameters:
position - of the target location.
lod - minimal lod assured by the new Holdback

removeHoldback

public void removeHoldback(IveObject holdback)
Deletes the given Holdback. This method can be called from the gui thread.

Parameters:
holdback - Holdback to be deleted

prevalidateHoldback

public boolean prevalidateHoldback(java.lang.String position)
Prevalidates the future position of the holdback. This method can be called from the gui thread.

Parameters:
position - of the target location.
Returns:
false iff the Holdback surely cannot be placed on the given location. But true does not necessarily assure successfull call to createHoldback.

getHoldbacks

public java.util.List<IveObject> getHoldbacks()
Retrieves the Holdback list. This method is intended to be called from the gui thread.

Returns:
copy of the list with all manually added Holdbacks.

getRefreshHook

public GuiHook getRefreshHook()
Getter for the Gui refresh hook.

Returns:
GuiHook signaled on every holdback list change.
